<fo:root xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" font-family="Helvetica" font-size="11pt">
  <fo:layout-master-set>
    <fo:simple-page-master master-name="A4" page-width="210mm" page-height="297mm"
        margin-top="22mm" margin-bottom="22mm" margin-left="22mm" margin-right="22mm">
      <fo:region-body margin-top="12mm" margin-bottom="14mm"/>
      <fo:region-before extent="10mm"/>
      <fo:region-after extent="10mm"/>
    </fo:simple-page-master>
  </fo:layout-master-set>
  <fo:page-sequence master-reference="A4">
    <fo:static-content flow-name="xsl-region-before">
      <fo:block font-size="9pt" color="#888888" border-after="0.5pt solid #cccccc" padding-after="2pt">Apache FOP for .NET &#8212; demonstration</fo:block>
    </fo:static-content>
    <fo:static-content flow-name="xsl-region-after">
      <fo:block font-size="9pt" color="#888888" text-align="center" border-before="0.5pt solid #cccccc" padding-before="2pt">Page <fo:page-number/></fo:block>
    </fo:static-content>
    <fo:flow flow-name="xsl-region-body">
      <fo:block font-size="22pt" font-weight="bold" color="#1a3c7b" space-after="10pt">Footnotes and cross-references</fo:block>
      <fo:block space-after="8pt" text-align="justify">This paragraph carries a footnote<fo:footnote><fo:inline font-size="7pt" color="#1a3c7b"> [1]</fo:inline><fo:footnote-body><fo:block font-size="9pt" color="#555555">[1] The footnote body is laid out at the bottom of the page, above the footer band, and its height reduces the space available to the body text.</fo:block></fo:footnote-body></fo:footnote>. It also cross-references a later section, which begins on page <fo:page-number-citation ref-id="endsection" font-weight="bold"/> &#8212; resolved by a two-pass layout.</fo:block>
      <fo:block background-color="#eef2fb" border="1pt solid #1a3c7b" padding="8pt" space-after="12pt" text-align="justify">Borders, padding and backgrounds are painted across page breaks; tables, lists, headers/footers, keeps and breaks are all supported.</fo:block>
      <fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 1. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 2. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 3. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 4. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 5. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 6. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical space and force pagination.</fo:block><fo:block space-after="6pt" text-align="justify">Paragraph 7. This document spans several pages so the running header and footer repeat and the footer page number increments. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog, repeatedly, to consume vertical sp